 and kernel basis 
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\mathbf{U}_{R}=\left[\begin{array}{rc}
-1 & x\\
-x^{2} & 0\\
-3x & 0\\
-3 & 0\\
0 & 1
\end{array}\right]
\]

\end_inset

 were given in Example 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "example1"

\end_inset

.
 The computation of the column basis also gives the right factor 
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\mathbf{V}_{U}=\left[\begin{array}{cccrr}
1 & 0 & 0 & 2 & -x\\
0 & 1 & 0 & 2x^{2} & 0\\
0 & 0 & 1 & -x & 0
\end{array}\right].
\]

\end_inset

Then 
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
{U}_{R}=\left[\begin{array}{rc}
-1 & 0\\
0 & 0\\
0 & 0\\
-3 & 0\\
0 & 1
\end{array}\right]~\mbox{and}~~{V}_{U}=\left[\begin{array}{cccrr}
1 & 0 & 0 & 2 & 0\\
0 & 1 & 0 & 0 & 0\\
0 & 0 & 1 & 0 & 0
\end{array}\right].
\]

\end_inset

A unimodular completion of 
\begin_inset Formula $U_{R}$
\end_inset

 is given by 
\family roman
\series medium
\shape up
\size normal
\emph off
\bar no
\strikeout off
